<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36097d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36097d">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36097d"> 97(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &apos;Tis a wise man / that never saw a / dead one.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A hundred years ago, it was so usual an occurrence to find a dead body in one of the lanes or alleys of &ldquo;The Island&rdquo; <font color="green">[Mud Island]</font>, that it occasioned no comment, and if any of the &ldquo;islanders&rdquo; had the bad taste to mention the matter, he would be told significantly&mdash;&ldquo;<mark>&apos;Tis a wise man that never saw &ldquo;a dead one</mark>&rdquo;. <small> Weston St. John Joyce, <a name="WSJ1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSJ1"><cite title="source">The Neighbourhood of Dublin</cite></a> (1921) 245</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
